From: ipod-sync vendoring
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] Fix struct stat -> GStatBuf for GLib 2.88's g_stat()

Modern GLib (2.88) types g_stat()'s second parameter as GStatBuf*
(= struct _stat64* on MinGW64), not struct stat*. Two call sites
in libgpod 0.8.0 declared the local as struct stat, which now
fails to compile with an incompatible-pointer-type error.

Fix is one-line per file: change "struct stat stat_buf;" to
"GStatBuf stat_buf;". The .st_size field is identical between the
two structs on MinGW, so no other changes are needed.

Apply with: cd <libgpod-src> && patch -p1 < 0002-*.patch
        or: cd <libgpod-src> && git apply 0002-*.patch
---
diff --git a/src/db-parse-context.c b/src/db-parse-context.c
index 88009c9..f4d4fe8 100644
--- a/src/db-parse-context.c
+++ b/src/db-parse-context.c
@@ -180,7 +180,7 @@ db_parse_context_new_from_file (const char *filename, Itdb_DB *db)
 	Itdb_Device *device;
 	GError* error;
 	GMappedFile* mapped_file;
-	struct stat stat_buf;
+	GStatBuf stat_buf;
 
 	ctx = NULL;
 	error = NULL;
diff --git a/src/itdb_tzinfo.c b/src/itdb_tzinfo.c
index ded4dd2..6305090 100644
--- a/src/itdb_tzinfo.c
+++ b/src/itdb_tzinfo.c
@@ -243,7 +243,7 @@ G_GNUC_INTERNAL void itdb_device_set_timezone_info (Itdb_Device *device)
     gint16 raw_timezone;
     gint timezone = 0;
     gboolean result;
-    struct stat stat_buf;
+    GStatBuf stat_buf;
     int status;
     char *prefs_path;
     guint offset;
